 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Sentiments, EXACTLY</span><hr size=1> If I were them, my next expansion would be only for highlevels, very much like Velious was last year. Most likely, it would involve only planes. I'd design some so a single group could work through one, as well as having some with the uberest of uber MoBs that would require tons of level 60s.<br>
<br>
I like the idea of separating high levels from low levels. In fact, I'd go another step, and add another 40 levels into the game. Once you ding to 61, your character dies, and you end up in the plane (or a demi-plane) of your diety. Then you start naked all over again, except you're an astral character instead of a lowbie mortal. One of the perks would be no more exp penalty on death. Another perk would be no more hell levels.<br>
<br>
I think the elite players need something that scares the crap outta them. Everything that Verant has given us seems to only be tough until the first insane guild beats it, and then it's no longer unknown. It's no longer scary.<br>
I used to be scared to death going on plane raids. But after going on a few, it's just like hunting anywhere else, except you've got alot of friends around.<br>
<br>
